  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7101.57 sitting right between the negative gamma pocket at 7115 (-3871.9M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5061.6M), dealers are likely oscillating between buying and selling flows as price whipsaws through these levels. The PIN regime with 54B+ in total GEX suggests strong mean-reversion dynamics, with dealers positioned to fade any directional moves and compress realized volatility. Key levels to watch: 7115 downside where dealer buying accelerates, and the 7150-7200 zone upside where heavy selling pressure kicks in from the stacked positive gamma walls.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy, range-bound trading between 7100-7150 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
